This paper deals with software engineering tasks such as test generation, fault localization, and test execution planning, which are typically covered under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The paper proposes a method to predict the trace of each test without executing it, based only on static properties of the test and the tested program, as well as past experience on different tests. This prediction is done by applying supervised learning, which falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of traces in automated troubleshooting, which is related to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The paper proposes a method to reduce the overhead of obtaining test traces, which is related to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques, which are covered under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
